        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Personalisation",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "prevention of biases (e.g., gender, racial, and age-related) in AI systems and data processing."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 15963,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "In addition, the proposed Act should more explicitly address the prevention of biases (e.g., gender, racial, and age-related) in AI systems and data processing. It should also include stronger provisions to tackle unfair discrimination against consumers.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s0",
          "section_path": [],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 37,
          "char_len": 254
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p21",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Design Patterns",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "dark patterns."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "topic": "Gaming",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "loot boxes,"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 25406,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Gaming platforms have become a popular space for children to spend their free time and interact with each other. However, they have also become where manipulative digital marketing practices are the most prevalent—designed to extend screentime and encourage in-game purchases through practices such as loot boxes, gamified incentives and dark patterns. Therefore, the proposed Act should place particular emphasis on the gaming sector, explicitly addressing and regulating these manipulative design features to ensure that consumers' vulnerabilities, especially those of children, are not exploited.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s1",
          "section_path": [
            "5. The gaming world"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 84,
          "char_len": 599
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p22",
        "items": [
          {
            "topic": "Gaming",
            "topic_source": "dfa",
            "evidence_quotes": [
              {
                "quote": "gaming platforms are not currently covered by the DSA."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 31547,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "The proposed Act should not merely serve as an additional layer of legislation on top of existing frameworks, but rather complement and strengthen the mechanisms already in place. For instance, it should clarify how it aligns with service design provisions under the Guidelines on the Protection of Minors established by the Digital Services Act (DSA), particularly since gaming platforms are not currently covered by the DSA. Similarly, the Act should address how it complements the AI Act in regulating the use of artificial intelligence for unfair or manipulative consumer practices.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s2",
          "section_path": [
            "6. Streamlining with other legislations"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 90,
          "char_len": 586
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p23",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 7549,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Even with well-drafted rules, enforcement remains a challenge. Differences in oversight and enforcement capacity among Member States risk creating unequal levels of consumer protection. Additionally, raising consumer awareness of their rights is essential for the Act to have real impact.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s3",
          "section_path": [
            "7. Effective enforcement"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 40,
          "char_len": 288
        }
      },
      {
        "para_id": "p24",
        "items": [],
        "meta": {
          "skipped": false,
          "skip_reason": null,
          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 8304,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Offlimits is the centre of expertise in the Netherlands combatting online transgressive behaviours, and the coordinator of the Dutch Safer Internet Centre (SIC). Offlimits operates the largest hotline in the European Union (EU) that processed over 603,000 URLs in 2024, swiftly identifying and facilitating the removal of illegal content, especially child sexual abuse material (CSAM). Offlimits also operates the helpline, which provides a channel for children, young people and adults alike to seek advice on dealing with various forms of online harm. One key importance of both the hotline and helpline lies in their ability to directly issue Notice and Takedown (NTD) orders to online service providers and platform operators, ensuring that CSAM and other illegal content is removed as quickly as possible from the internet, while actively following up with platforms that fail to comply. Over the years, Offlimits has built trusted partnership with major online platforms such as Meta and Snap. As a trusted partner, Offlimits can send NTDs through a dedicated channel for quicker response from the platforms. In 2025, Offlimits became the first recognised Trusted Flagger under the Digital Services Act (DSA) in the Netherlands, demonstrating our expertise and competence in recognising and reporting illegal content, and that NTDs sent by Offlimits need to be prioritised and treated with due diligence. Additionally, Offlimits operates the prevention line, providing a crucial early intervention service in the fight against child sexual abuse by offering support to anyone who has concerns about his or her sexual feelings and/or behaviour towards minors.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s4",
          "section_path": [
            "About Offlimits"
          ],
          "span": null,
          "chunk_quality": "ok",
          "chunk_word_count": 254,
          "char_len": 1664
        }
